---  
const pageTitle = "Shadow Projection";  
---  

<html lang="en">  
  <head>  
    <meta charset="utf-8" />  
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />  
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>  
    <style>  
      :root {  
        --paper: #ffffff;  
        --ink: #000000;  
        --line: #000000;  
        --soft: #efefef;  
        --blue: #0000ee;  
        --red: #cc0000;  
        --green: #008000;  
      }  

      html, body {  
        margin: 0;  
        padding: 0;  
        background: var(--paper);  
        color: var(--ink);  
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;  
        font-size: 18px;  
        line-height: 1.55;  
      }  

      a { text-decoration: underline; }  
      a.blue { color: var(--blue); }  
      a.red { color: var(--red); }  
      a.green { color: var(--green); }  

      .page {  
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));  
        margin: 0 auto;  
        padding: 28px 0 60px;  
      }  

      .topbar {  
        border: 1px solid var(--line);  
        padding: 10px 14px;  
        margin-bottom: 18px;  
        text-align: center;  
        background: #fafafa;  
      }  

      .frame {  
        border: 1px solid var(--line);  
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;  
      }  

      h1 {  
        font-size: 40px;  
        text-align: center;  
        margin: 0 0 8px;  
      }  

      .subtitle {  
        text-align: center;  
        font-size: 16px;  
        margin-bottom: 24px;  
      }  

      .divider {  
        text-align: center;  
        margin: 18px 0 24px;  
      }  

      p { margin-bottom: 16px; }  

      .quote {  
        margin: 22px auto;  
        max-width: 680px;  
        border: 1px solid var(--line);  
        padding: 14px;  
        background: var(--soft);  
        font-style: italic;  
        text-align: center;  
      }  

      .section-title {  
        font-size: 28px;  
        text-align: center;  
        margin: 34px 0 16px;  
      }  

      .mini-links {  
        text-align: center;  
        margin-top: 30px;  
      }  

      .mini-links a {  
        margin: 0 10px;  
      }  

      .footer-note {  
        text-align: center;  
        margin-top: 26px;  
        font-size: 14px;  
      }  
    </style>  
  </head>  
  <body>  
    <div class="page">  
      <div class="topbar">  
        [ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]  
        [ <a class="blue" href="/foundations">foundations index</a> ]  
        [ <a class="green" href="/foundations/individuation">previous</a> ]  
        [ <a class="red" href="/foundations/what-is-the-self">next</a> ]  
      </div>  

      <main class="frame">  
        <h1>Shadow Projection</h1>  
        <p class="subtitle">foundations / shadow / archive entry 004</p>  

        <div class="divider">***</div>  

        <p>  
          What you see in others is not always about them.  
        </p>  

        <p>  
          Sometimes it is something within you, being reflected back.  
        </p>  

        <div class="quote">  
          The shadow is not what you are. It is what you refuse to see.  
        </div>  

        <h2 class="section-title">what is the shadow</h2>  

        <p>  
          The shadow is everything you have rejected, denied, or pushed away in yourself.  
        </p>  

        <p>  
          Traits that were judged as wrong, weak, embarrassing, or unacceptable become hidden.  
        </p>  

        <p>  
          But they do not disappear. They remain alive in the unconscious.  
        </p>  

        <h2 class="section-title">projection</h2>  

        <p>  
          When something in the shadow is too uncomfortable to face, the mind places it onto others.  
        </p>  

        <p>  
          You begin to see in others what you cannot accept in yourself.  
        </p>  

        <div class="quote">  
          Strong reactions are often mirrors.  
        </div>  

        <p>  
          Intense anger, jealousy, admiration, or disgust can point toward something within you that is asking to be seen.  
        </p>  

        <h2 class="section-title">why it matters</h2>  

        <p>  
          If projection is not recognized, you remain divided.  
        </p>  

        <p>  
          You fight parts of yourself without knowing it.  
        </p>  

        <p>  
          Relationships become distorted because you are not seeing others clearly.  
        </p>  

        <h2 class="section-title">integration</h2>  

        <p>  
          The goal is not to eliminate the shadow.  
        </p>  

        <p>  
          The goal is to become aware of it and bring it into consciousness.  
        </p>  

        <p>  
          This requires honesty and the willingness to look where you normally avoid.  
        </p>  

        <p>  
          This is a core step in <a class="green" href="/foundations/individuation">individuation</a>.  
        </p>  

        <div class="mini-links">  
          <a class="blue" href="/foundations">back to foundations index</a>  
          <a class="blue" href="/foundations/what-is-the-self">continue to: what is the self</a>  
          <a class="red" href="/dreams/active-imagination">active imagination</a>  
          <a class="green" href="/self/creativity-and-fantasy">creativity</a>  
        </div>  

        <p class="footer-note">what you reject returns in another form.</p>  
      </main>  
    </div>  
  </body>  
</html>